item.title: Samuel Eto'O 1st Goal for Anji v Rostov (Y. Zhirkov assist ) August 27th, 2011
item.description:
Samuel Eto'O 1st Goal for Anji v Rostov (Y. Zhirkov assist ) August 27th, 2011
Saturday, August 27th, 2011Samuel Eto'o's surprise move to Russia, considering the climate, potential racial abuse and lack of sporting challenge, was all about one thing: Money. Moolah. Cash. Dough. Dollars. Pounds. Euros. Roubles. The bottom line to the deal was as follows: Price: 25 million euros per year (£21.8m) Which translates into£1,458,333m per month, £364,583 per wk, £52,083 per day, £2,170 per hour, £36.16 per minute, 60p per second. Fair play to a striker that has shown he can score goals anywhere. And, Anzhi did get some return from their investment, a debut goal after the Cameroon striker came on as a 58th minute substitute at Rostov. Eto'o might want to thank fellow new Anzhi employee Yuri Zhirkov who made most of the running for the goal, drifting in between two players. Первый гол Самуеля Это'о в РПЛ!
